Package: structest
Title: Testing the Structural Interpretation of a Univariate Latent Factor Model
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Felipe", "Fontana Vieira", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "felipelfv98@gmail.com")
Description: Implements two statistical tests from VanderWeele and Vansteelandt
    (2022) <doi:10.1111/rssb.12555> to reject the structural interpretation of
    a univariate latent factor model. The T0 test (Section 3.2 of the paper)
    depends on reliability estimates and requires at least 3 indicators and an
    auxiliary variable with at least 2 levels. The T1 test (Section 3.3) is
    reliability-independent and requires at least 2 indicators and an auxiliary
    variable with at least 3 levels.
